  "A company's daily profit is P(x) = −x² + 40x − 300 dollars, where x is the number of items sold. By graphing, determine the range of items that must be sold to make a profit (P > 0).": "",
  "Exactly 20 items": "",
  "Between 0 and 20 items": "",
  "Between 10 and 30 items": "",
  "More than 40 items": "",
  "Set P(x) = 0: −x² + 40x − 300 = 0, or x² − 40x + 300 = 0. Factoring: (x − 10)(x − 30) = 0, so x = 10 and x = 30. The profit is positive between the zeros: 10 < x < 30.": "",
  "A fountain shoots water in a parabolic arc described by y = −0.5x² + 4x, where x and y are in feet. What is the maximum height of the water and how far from the base does it land?": "",
